Consequently, there is a strong societal consensus that views homosexuality as contrary to the established moral, cultural, and religious norms of the country. This is also reflected in the current legal framework, as well as the broader societal discourse, which tends to view traditional marriage as the fundamental building block of society. While there is increasing exposure to global human rights discussions, public sentiment remains overwhelmingly conservative on this specific issue, reflecting a collective commitment to maintaining traditional societal standards.

